    "term":'<p><strong>A 50-year-old man presents with fatigue and is found to have leukocytosis with circulating blasts, anemia, and thrombocytopenia. Flow cytometry of the blood reveals B-lineage lymphoblasts. Karyotype shows the t(9;22) (q34;q11.2).</strong></p><p class="box-green-border"><strong>What is the diagnosis and how does the karyotype affect treatment recommendations?</strong></p>',
