    "imageonly":true,
    "defination" :[
      {
        "title":"",
        "phase": '<p><strong>MRI or CT myelography of the entire spine should be performed in a myeloma patient with symptoms of cord compression.</strong></p><p>Patients with myeloma can develop spinal cord compression from an extramedullary plasmacytoma or vertebral fracture. This is a medical emergency which requires immediate imaging of the spine along with consultation with Neurosurgery and Radiation Oncology and initiation of high-dose glucocorticoid therapy to avoid permanent neurologic dysfunction.</p><div class="suggested_readings"><p>Suggested Readings:</p><p><em>Br J Haematol</em>. 2015;171:332<span class="aria_label" role="text" aria-label="To"><span aria-hidden="true">-</span></span>343.</p><p>Greer JP, Arber DA, Glader BE, List AF, Means RT Jr, Rodgers GM. <em>Wintrobe&apos;s Clinical Hematology</em>. 14th ed. Wolters Kluwer; 2018.</p><p>Kaushansky K, Prchal JT, Burns LJ, Lichtman MA, Levi M, Linch DC. <em>Williams Hematology</em>. 10th ed. McGraw Hill; 2021.</p></div>'
      }
    ]
